# Cloudflare Pages cache rules.
# HTML documents must always revalidate: a redeploy changes the hashed chunk
# names, and a stale cached document would ask for chunks that no longer exist
# (404 -> ChunkLoadError). Revalidating the document keeps it in step with the
# assets it references. The hashed build assets are immutable, so cache hard.
# (Later, more-specific rules take precedence on Cloudflare Pages.)

/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate

/_next/static/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
